1
00:00:00,260 --> 00:00:03,359
We are now in the priest’s room

2
00:00:03,384 --> 00:00:08,776
The late priest Arakel used to sit here

3
00:00:08,854 --> 00:00:13,255
I met him two or three times

4
00:00:13,280 --> 00:00:14,714
In this room

5
00:00:14,739 --> 00:00:17,318
There was a desk and a chair here

6
00:00:17,343 --> 00:00:23,802
And here were chairs or couches where church guests sat

7
00:00:23,957 --> 00:00:31,119
Christian parties also used to meet the priest here

8
00:00:31,144 --> 00:00:36,692
In this room, which served as the parish office

9
00:00:36,717 --> 00:00:44,229
Or the priest’s office, through which church services were provided

10
00:00:44,256 --> 00:00:46,651
Such as issuing baptism certificates

11
00:00:46,676 --> 00:00:49,308
Or marriage certificates

12
00:00:49,333 --> 00:00:52,303
That is, wedding records as they are called

13
00:00:52,328 --> 00:00:58,292
And also in this room, funeral arrangements for any Armenian were made

14
00:00:58,317 --> 00:01:04,047
To agree on the rituals

15
00:01:04,072 --> 00:01:10,792
And ceremonies for burying any member of the Armenian parish
